<br>
Tribe: Queen of Sisters of Honor, Tribal Healer for the Shatomlic Amazons<br>
<br>
Character Type* (mortal, demi): Mortal       <br>
<br>
Character Class (warrior, bard, etc.): Royalty, Healer<br>
<br>
A brief description of your character (physical appearance, personality): Rhiannon has shoulder length red hair, and blue-green eyes. She's about 5'. She is 20 years old. She is not as built as a warrior, but is strong in the everyday work sense. She is shy, but friendly and quick with a smile. She is fair-minded, and fiercely loyal. And she expects the same loyalty in return. As a Queen, when she first starts out, she is rather hesitant. She was not trained for royalty, and so is afraid of making a mistake.<br>
<br>
Skills.  Main weapon is the Long Staff. she also has minor skills with a spear. the majority of her skills lie in Healing(with herbs, and even magic), and some priestess-craft. she has an affinity for animals of all kinds.  Her native language is Gaelic. She speaks Greek and can read it a little, and also can speak the amazon language, but cannot read it.<br>
<br>
Rhia's Horse:  Fionna, a white/grey speckled  Abyssinian mare.<br>
<br>
Relevant histoy: Her homeland is Hybernia, she was born to Hefeydd the Old. She was later betrothed to Pwyll, the Lord of Dyffed, at the age of 14. They married and had a child. But on the night their son was born he(the child) was stolen. Rhiannon was framed for the crime of killing the babe, by her, and her husband cast her out. She left Eire, and wound up in Gaul, where she was taken by Romans and sold into slavery to a Greek merchant family. She was not beaten, but was not treated kindly either. She was with them for about 4 years when she was travelling with the merchant, and they were attacked. In the midst of the fray she managed to hide in the woods. She stole a horse from the nearest town, and rode for days. She finally ended up smack dab in the middle of Hyrcania and was taken in by the Shatomlic tribe. She was taught their ways and initiated into the tribe. Shortly afterwards, she was going around visiting some of the other tribes to learn new healing method s and came upon the SoH. When the Queen was killed, she gave Rhiannon her right of caste, and she took the old Queen's place.<br>
<br>
